{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place leeks and ¼ tsp salt into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add sweet potatoes and chop a further <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water, stock paste, vanilla bean seeds and vanilla bean pod, cider vinegar, ginger and white pepper and cook <b>15 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile 3-5 minutes before purée is finished cooking, begin heating a skillet over medium-high heat.","Add oil to skillet, season scallops with ½ tsp salt and pepper and cook until browned (approx. 2 min. per side). Transfer to a plate and keep warm.","Add milk to mixing bowl and purée <b>1 min\/speed 5<b><strong>-10<\/strong> increasing speed gradually. Adjust seasoning to taste.","To serve, divide sweet potato purée between two plates and top with seared scallops. Garnish with arugula and blackberries and serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["3 oz leeks, white part only, cut into pieces","¾ tsp salt, divided","6 oz sweet potatoes, peeled, cut into pieces (approx. 1 sm.)","8 oz water","1 tsp vegetable stock paste","½ vanilla bean, seeds scraped out (optional)","1 tsp apple cider vinegar","½ tsp ground ginger","1 pinch ground white pepper, to taste","2 tbsp olive oil","6 jumbo sea scallops, cleaned, patted dry with paper towels","½ tsp ground black pepper","3 oz whole milk","baby arugula, to garnish","8 blackberries, to garnish"]}],"id":"r307844","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-nOpJafrGZb4\/XZMuUodIWTI\/AAAAAAAAaD8\/MQg4liY0Aggu3JefXupCFiMRFkX-g9PnQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_GH435lyd0r5ATDg8.png","title":"Seared Scallops with Sweet Potato Purée","publishedAt":"2018-02-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30 g","fat":"19 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"35 g","calories":"1753 kJ \/ 419 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cast iron skillet (9 in.)","basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","2 portions"]}